social_posts.post_text: My youngest and I went into the city to the Christkindlmarket ❄️ We had a fun time! Chicago is the best city 🏙️

I’m still thinking about and still posting some of my favorite pictures from the Lightscape evening we had at the @chicagobotanic garden last month. Just such a beautiful night even though it was cold. 🌳🥶 I thought about not going because it was 18 degrees F but I’m so happy I did. This was quite possibly the littlest risk you could take but I’m dropping these photos here to remind myself to step out of my comfort zone ☺️ Because of the reach of the algorithm, no one is going to get this on their feeds anyway, so I’m posting this for me ❤️

I love my local library and l, now that break is almost here, I’m loading up to read and learn with all my free time 😆 But seriously you don’t need to buy books to enjoy them. Your library can lend them to you and if they don’t have the book you want, they can interlibrary loan it in! I also love just hanging out at the library 🤓 What are you reading???
The next video in my latest series on Successful Treatment of R is premiering tomorrow 🎞️ R is a tough, tough sound to treat https://youtube.com/@SarahWuSLP

👋 I’m going to do one of those awkward posts where I introduce myself because there’s “so many new people here.” Spoiler alert: there are no new people here. Why? Because I’m not good at this platform. I just need to owe that fact. Anyway, this was me last week at Universal Studios Islands of Adventure with my sons! We were at the Poseidon show, which was fun. But life is not all rainbows because this trip was right after the worst Xmas of our lives: Covid finally found our family and hit everyone but me. This trip almost didn’t happen because the boys had to test negative to go and thankfully they did. My husband was not part of the Orlando trip because he was still sick at home. Covid’s effects have still lingered for him, which I knew would happen (due to his asthma) and which was why we have been so very careful all this time. In case you are wondering, we will continue to mask. Anyway, this photo is me trying to enjoy a trip that gave us a ray of light from what otherwise was a hellish winter break. The latest with me: I’ve started my fourth semester as a clinical supervisor with a university and third semester as an adjunct. It’s great work, just low pay, that I enjoy immensely. My only wish right now is for my husband to get back to his baseline health. ❤️
Happy Lunar New Year 🧧 It’s the year of the rabbit, which is my husband’s year. He is the most deserving of a tremendous year 🎊🐰 These red envelopes are for the boys from their grandparents ☺️

My to do list is loooonnnnggggg and I have virtually no social life. So then, in a group text thread, I decided to suggest starting a book club with my older son’s friends’ moms. They chose this book. I have to finish it in a month. Can I do it? 😬 I hear good things

I haven’t been on here much and honestly I can say my mental health improved. The first pic was a week ago when I finally got strict with myself. 💪 The second pic was today: my screen time went up a bit this past week. You can put limits on screen time under Settings -> Screen Time -> App Limits 📲 Mine is set for 15 minutes for all social media combined. When I reach that time, I get “locked out,” which I can immediately add another 15 minutes, but typically it snaps me out of a scrolling trance and I get back to living my real life.

Library cookbook haul 👩🏼‍🍳 I love to cook but I have such little time. Seriously hit up your local library for the best books. No need to buy them! Also your library can Interlibrary loan books they don’t have from other libraries 📚
Do you like what I put in the wall in my office at work? I even thought about making them for e-t-s-y for others because it’s just so cheerful 😄 Thoughts?
My desk at work: mini-fan, mini-purifier, mega “hanitizer,” pens, and a mini-fake plant. The fake plant is my favorite, in case you are wondering🪴
How surprised were we when searching for a quarter for the Aldi cart!? 😱😍🤩 This one’s a keeper!
I mean, right???!!! #slphumor
Still uploading speech therapy videos to my channel 🎥 If you are looking for a specific video, feel free to suggest one! Next week’s video is going to be about eliminating nasalization 👃

I’m not sure why I like this picture, but I do. It was when we were at Universal Studios in early January. This is me at almost 45.5 - my half-birthday is coming up 🌟 I usually have my hair in a ponytail. I’m wearing my favorite baseball cap that I got in 2021 at an Angels game in California. And I’m wearing a 5k t-shirt, one of many that I have hanging around. I think I like this photo because one of my boys took it and I think this might be how they view me. And that’s okay with me ❤️😎
Still chugging along on ye olde blog 👵🏻 Have you caught my latest stuff? I also went off topic for once and wrote an epic post detailing our trip to Orlando. All in the spirit of helping 😎

The ‘rona is still out there 🦠 I know I’m a big downer by saying that but you can still wear a mask when you feel sick or you are around large groups of people. I work with graduate students, college students, and kids. If I didn’t mask, I’d be sick constantly. I have never tested positive for COVID and my last illness was in September 🤞 But my youngest son just caught strep so let’s hope I miss that one too!
I started a book club with the moms of my oldest son’s friends. This was the choice for the second book. I got it from @thriftbooks 📖 Anyone read it? Thoughts?
IKEA is a secret place to find affordable speech therapy materials! Come explore with me 😎 @ikeausa

Can you see why I wear sunglasses? Gotta hide the bags 😬 But go back to your textbooks because at the base of Maslow’s Hierarchy of Needs is SLEEP 😴 Kids and adults alike are running a deficit. It’s an epidemic actually
Speech Path VS ChatGPT - Episode 1: the CH sound - Speech path wins 🏆
Speech Path vs ChatGPT- Episode 2: SH sound - the machine totally missed the fact you need to round your lips for the SH sound!! Ha ha, take that AI 🤓 SLP FOR THE WIN 🥇

What I’m reading now “All The Light We Cannot See” by Anthony Doerr. The second shot is the blurb inside the front cover. It is about World War II. This has been sitting in my “to be read” pile forever. It is well-written for sure, maybe too wordy? So far it is good and holding my attention because I want to see what is going to happen to the characters. I’m such a fickle reader 🤓 I couldn’t finish “Chemistry Lessons” for my book club earlier this year, but I did finish “The Lost Apothecary” for our May book club meeting 🥳 I really enjoyed that book. I decided to grab “All The Light We Cannot See” off my shelf since I have this space of time before our next book club pick. Have you read this? It’s been around for some time so it’s at the library 📚

social_posts.post_text: This is a long one but I wanted you to know how I fixed my chronic greasy hair problem (a problem I’ve had for 20+ years) in 7-10 days. It was one small adjustment in the shower!! 🚿

Here’s your Friday reminder: you can’t pour from an empty cup! I just took a moment to pseudo-meditate, closing my eyes and trying to go blank for a couple minutes. Felt great. Nothing a little quiet moment, 1000 mg of acetaminophen, and a strong black tea can’t fix! TGIF 🥳 Shout out to @smilesforspeech - a wonderful organization led by a dynamic leader. Check them out 💛

Here’s what I’m reading now 🧐 “Tomorrow and Tomorrow and Tomorrow” by Gabrielle Zevin @gabriellezevin and “The Fortunes of Jaded Women” by Carolyn Huynh @carolynkhuynh - they look so good! I’ve started “Tomorrow” and it’s cute. Way more uplifting than the previous book I read (All the Light We Cannot See). I need something a little lighter 📚 Have you read or heard of these books? 🤓

World’s most random video: my key chains! The bright orange my older son made at summer camp is the best because I can always spot my keys in my crowded purse. I also like my CCC-SLP keychain from @speechbuddies 😍 Thank you! And finally “I get my kicks on Route 66” - my youngest son bought it for me at LAX!! 😂😆

Can you believe the Supreme Court decided short-term corporate earnings matter more than life? Water is the base of life. It’s at the bottom of the Maslow’s Hierarchy of Needs pyramid. It’s not worth jeopardizing our future for some company. Vote for politicians and policy that protect our environment. Your Brita pitcher can’t make you safe from this. @earthjustice
Cleared out my son’s backpack and found his “witing” notebook 🤣 I guess it’s a “wap” on this school year 🤪

It’s summer and I’m reading at the ballpark while my kids play ⚾️ This has been on my shelf for a long time (end of 2021) but finally getting to it. I’m enjoying it so far. What are you reading this summer?

Least sexy, most functional IG post ever 😇 Here in our bathroom this winter I organized what I call the “Sick Box” which has everything a parent managing a sick kid can easily grab and go. The box has the ear thermometer, children’s meds, bandaids, neosporin cream, icy hot cream (for sore muscles - it’s baseball season), pulse ox, COVID tests, and our salt lamp 😉 We actually only had one brief illness this spring that only hit the kids (masks for the win). Speaking of which, the second picture is of our big box of masks and hand sannie, which is by the front door for easy grab and go. We have surgical masks, KN95s, and you can’t see the N95s in the far back. I haven’t been sick since September 🤞but COVID came for a visit in December. I was able to avoid it by masking with the N95 and I was spraying Lysol too (not a fan but it is helpful at times). Anyway, I thought this might be helpful for you guys to see if you need inspo for easy organization of stuff to help make your lives easier ✨
I’m organizing and I’m reminded just how much of a paper and pen person I am. Is it a Gen X thing? 🧐🤓
How about a quiet Jenga?! 🤯 Who thought of this? It’s brilliant! #speechtherapy #speechtherapytips
Another cool find at Target! Happy Salmon - how fun for following directions goals ✋ #speechtherapyideas

🎵 Chicago, I love you 🎵 My husband and I made our way into the city for The Lyric Opera of Chicago’s @lyricopera production of West Side Story 🎤 The orchestra, the singing, the acting, the dancing, and all of the athleticism was so incredible 🤩 We actually won our tickets from the Chicago Tribune @chicagotribune 🗞️Chicago is the best! Topics and themes in West Side Story production are still relevant today, believe it or not 💔
“Let’s Get Talking” seems like a fun way to build rapport in speech therapy sessions #speechtherapyideas

Did somebody lose a bound morpheme? Because I found one just lying on the sidewalk 🧐🤪😂
(Bad SLP joke? Ok, I’ll show myself out…😅)
Sometimes you need to get away 🧳 We are up north for a family reunion. When we aren’t in the water, we like to take time to visit one of our favorite places to get tea 🫖@tillys_rhinelander
Hedbanz are a speech room staple! I saw this “mini” set that was dinosaur-themed at Walgreens for just six bucks 🤯🦕 🦖 Run 🏃🏼‍♀️ #speechtherapygames
Are you on Instagram’s new app @threadsapp ? It’s great because it’s mostly plain old words! I love it 🥰

Jenga feels like a purposeless game to me, I hate to say it. That’s why finding the game Jenga Maker guides kids to build according to plan and helps visual-motor skills 👀 🤚 #speechpathology #speechtherapygames
I’m trying to check out and I’m like “wHaT iS wRoNg” 🤪
We’ve been married for 2️⃣0️⃣ years today 🎉🥳🥰
I was inspired by the coffee sleeve from @kremacoffeeroasters in Lockport. ☕️ What powerful words! 🗣️
Can you spot the ❤️?? My youngest son lay down in the grass and then asked for my phone! Enjoy this special moment of summer zen with the sound of the cicadas coming through
Ravinia = Chicago Symphony Orchestra = very small 20th wedding anniversary celebration = a couple old close friends and their kids = perfection ✨

Another speech therapy find at Target 🎯 Linkee is a card game with four different describing words that can be linked to one noun. How fun for speech therapy!! #speechtherapy #speechtherapyideas #speechtherapygames

Find a kid that doesn’t like playing The Floor is Lava! But now you have an actual board game. This is the “Hot Zone” edition. Not sure what that means but I think this is great to use to get out some gross motor wiggles before tackling fine motor goals! 🔥
I’ve been working on and off from a coworking space and it is nice to get out of the house. Great to have a professional background for online classes 🗣️

Poetry for Neanderthals is a game that is similar to Taboo where you have to have a partner guess a word printed on the card, but here you can only use words that are ONE SYLLABLE. If you say a two syllable word, you get bonked on the head with an inflatable club!!! My sons love this game and my husband does a terrific Neanderthal impression to boot (he’s really good with impressions). We have too much fun playing this at home, but I’m thinking the inflatable club might be a bit too much for the speech therapy room! 😅🤣
Did you hear about the ASHFoundation’s 5K in August? You can join virtually or in-person 🏃🏼‍♀️ and support scholarships for CSD professionals. @ashaweb ashfoundationcsd

I’m finally getting around to “A Man Called Ove” 👏 I bought it on @thriftbooks and it’s a used library book (peep 👀 the library 😜). The first book I read from this author was Anxious People (and I LOVED IT), which was probably one of my favorite books ever. I would say I’m about 1/6 of the way through A Man Called Ove. It hasn’t grabbed me yet, but there’s still much more to go. The second photo is of the @chicagotribune because I’m a subscriber 🗞️ to the Sunday edition for ages and ages. I want to support journalism and I also like reading a real paper. My husband always reads the sports section and my youngest always reads the comics. It’s a thing we do every Sunday. 📖
This is your sign to put a time limit on all your social apps and live your life away from a screen ❤️

My phone reminded me that a year ago I went to Pilsen (neighborhood in Chicago) to visit the National Museum of Mexican Art @explorenmma 💫 While I was there, I walked around Pilsen and marveled at the murals 😍 These are just a couple that I saw that day. There are so many. Just a reminder to go do stuff before it gets cold 😅 I also think we need way more public art!!

How fun is Upwords!? It’s like scrabble but you go up, changing one letter at a time. I think this is perfect for students with phonological awareness deficits to practice these skills in a playful way. Have you worked with older students with phonological awareness difficulties? I have and this would be perfect for them! #speechtherapygames #phonologicalawareness #upwords #speechtherapyideas

I had a fun day at The Art Institute of Chicago @artinstitutechi and I highly recommend it. We saw so much great art (even medieval weaponry) and my sons thought it was great fun to see everything and I know they learned a few things too. 🖼️ Not pictured: our delicious lunch 🥗

“What do you meme? Family edition” is a fun game that my family actually owns and plays at home. My older elementary aged son thinks it’s hysterical and I think the game can be easily adapted to that age and above in speech therapy sessions to work on inference for skills or even “theory of mind” where you think about what another person might be thinking. Highly recommend 👍 #speechtherapy #speechtherapyideas #speechtherapygames

The Chicago Botanic Garden is my happy place. We went there over the weekend and it was serene 🧘‍♀️ These pictures are flowers from above. I just like nature so much and savoring everything before the cold returns 🌬️ @chicagobotanic

Just have to relive our trip to the Art Institute of Chicago @artinstitutechi last week. Here are some of our favorites from the “old building” including Seurat, Renoir, Toulouse-Lautrec, Degas, Monet, Van Gogh, etc. To stand in front of art that has stood the test of time is a tremendous feeling 🤩 Later I’ll share some modern art from the “new building” (modern wing) 🎨

I’m a little crabby 🦀 No, I’m not crabby at all; I’m talking about a game 😆 Anyway, this is a card game that you play in teams. When you get four of the same, you have to send a secret signal to your partner. They have to pick up on it and yell “you’re a little crabby” BUT if the other team intercepts that signal and yells “I’m a little crabby” first, you lose points 😝 This could be fun in speech therapy sessions with older students who have trouble picking up on facial expressions! 🦀 #imalittlecrabby #speechtherapygames

Meet my sister @hollyanneburns 👯‍♀️ Last week had a little lunchtime meetup and outing at the @andersonjapanesegardens and it was just what we needed ✨ It’s nice to hang out without kids and wander around a new place! 🥰 By the way, can you tell that I’m the oldest? I imagine you’re not surprised! I have all the characteristics of an older sister, good and bad!

The modern wing of the Art Institute of Chicago is interesting for sure, but the vibe is completely different than the main galleries. We got to see Warhol, Rothgo, Pollack, and they were cool to see in person 😎 The pictures I’m sharing here are fine but there was some shocking art in that area with more “modern” naked pictures, you could say. My kids were like 😳 @artinstitutechi
Some additional images from my trip to the Anderson Japanese Gardens @andersonjapanesegardens 🌱 It’s a compact, calming place that is perfect for a day trip. Their food in the cafe was excellent too.
Chicago Botanic Garden 🪴 is my happy place 😍 @chicagobotanic

🙈Digging into our storage space was actually fun because I unearthed boxes and boxes of speech therapy material I packed away in 2016. I thought there might be a day in the future where I would need them again and now’s the time! 🤓 Although I feel like a hoarder, I’m happy to have them and I hope I don’t have to store them again 📦 I literally never want to box them up again!! I think I’d probably give them away than do this again, but I’m happy to see them. Getting inspired all over again 💡
If you zoom in, you can see my oldest practicing his pitching in the park. THIS is why I don’t want summer to end 🌞 My whole family lives for outdoor time ⚾️
🤣 Follow along as I refill my mini Tylenol stash 🤣

The Bluffaneer says it’s a dice game but the dice are those bone-like “keys” 🤔 Each player has a stash of pirate coins and has to find matches with the pirate cards and symbols. This is easily modifiable for speech sound articulation goals your clients have!! 🏴‍☠️ Especially those kids who love pirates 🏴‍☠️

We happened upon a Tower Records pop up in Highland Park at @madamezuzus to celebrate @smashingpumpkins 30th anniversary of the release of their album 💿 It was cool to be there, especially for my husband because he’s always been a music geek. The Smashing Pumpkins are live-streaming a concert tomorrow (Sunday night) at 9 pm to celebrate. In-person tickets are sold out but you can steam it for free 🎧

Finding tennis at age 44 has been the best thing ever. 🎾 I play at the local indoor tennis facility operated by the park district. I’ve been playing now, taking group lessons, since August 2022 so now it been almost 13 months. Not taking my health for granted because someone I know had a severe sprain occur on the court, I also take it easy and I do wear a mask because people come in and play sick 🙅🏼‍♀️ Playing tennis helps me stay fit and it’s so so fun. If you are in Chicagoland and want someone to hit around with, let me know. I’m still a beginner but I LOVE it. I’m so competitive that I’m better in our pretend matches than in our drills 🤨 My 46th birthday is on the horizon and I really hope to play for a really long time 💗 I’m someone who never enjoyed P.E. in school and hates working out so this is huge for me 💗
These pumpkins 🎃 caught my eye. Do you love the colors of fall too? 🍁

Somewhere along the journey of life I got old. And so did all my friends. And I could actually be the mother of multiple coworkers. Yep, I would have had to have had them in college, but they could be my children. Aging is humbling, but I’m so lucky. I’ve lost high school friends over the years who didn’t get the privilege of aging. Cancer and motor vehicle accidents took them too early. I’m grateful to be here. And I’m here in large part due to modern medicine. I trust science and that will never change. I mask in indoor public spaces still. Hey, I want to be here for as long as I can and the ‘Rona is still out there and no one is sure if we should be getting it over and over. On Monday I got the flu shot and the new ‘Rona booster shot at the same time. No side effects, in fact my arms hurt for a bit and that was it. So I won’t throw away my shot and maybe you should consider it too 💉Also if you are of a certain age or have certain medical conditions, you could even get the RSV and pneumonia vaccines too. Talk to your doctor. (Negative comments will be deleted)

Who here loves #popuppirate for articulation therapy with reluctant-to-practice students? Makes speech fun because of the surprise factor! Which sword will finally make him pop up? #speechtherapy #speechtherapyideas #speechtherapygames

We were in the city a couple weeks ago and snapped this picture of the lobby of The Chicago Athletic Assn Hotel 🤯 @chicagoathletichotel Honestly it left me speechless 🤩 They have a shake shack there on the ground floor and that’s where we were grabbing a bite. I never even knew it existed before! #chicagohiddengems
Do you see what I see? Is the pepper in a good mood? Swipe ➡️ Or is it just that I’m happy tomorrow is Friday? 😊
Wow, things got loud at the ball field during my son’s game today! My watch got concerned ⌚️ I’ve never gotten this alert before 🤯 As an SLP this alert makes me happy to see!

I adore you Chicago 🏙️ I snapped this a few weeks ago when we were downtown. Here’s your reminder to enjoy the now. The weather was sublime this summer and now fall weather is here. Not my favorite, but I feel like I got a lot of sunshine this summer so I am in an okay place: I can accept fall is essentially here now🍁🍂

Leaving you with this beautiful thought 💭 I feel like we need more walkable communities so we can have these moments of connection. For me, and I’m sure like many of you, even when we buy things “in-person,” it requires getting in a car and driving there. I’m not chatting people up at Target either, though sometimes I do talk to the cashier and that’s pleasant. Sadly, I’m so time broke with work that online shopping is a lifeline most of the time. One of my goals in life is to live in a walkable community. I just haven’t gotten there yet. ✨
👏The big AAC app sale starts in just a few days 👏  I don’t work with AAC much these days but I’ve seen LAMP in both English and Spanish and it’s just so cool 📲

My friend Kim @kiminthewest has written a stunning book that is out today 💓 Her writing is honestly poetic and haunting in all the right ways. I can’t wait to dig in. It’s about their family’s experience living in Las Vegas and supporting the community there with food, their community right in their midst. I remember when she first moved there from NYC and it was a shift in her life that made everything come into focus for her, in terms of what she is on this Earth to do: write brilliant truths. “The Meth Lunches” will be a page turner -and it’s non-fiction- that will change you. I also encourage you to get on her substack because everything she writes keeps you thinking for days afterwards. You are an incredible human 🩷 I get to call you a friend and I’ve even visited your home in Vegas back in 2015 -and seen the kitchen where you make the magic happen. One day I’ll visit again. Congrats on pub day 🎉

Do you love spending time in bookstores? Then you will have to break up with Jeff Bezos and start shopping at bookstores in your area. Because they need you. In my area there are no more independent bookstores left, but we do have @barnesandnoble and I'm grateful for that. Addicted to online shopping? I bought a book from Barnes and Noble's website and picked it up in store. The price was the same as Jeff Bezos price. And it just felt so great to be in a bookstore 📚I want bookstores to stay in my community ❤️

I stumbled into this book at the library and now I'm wondering how did I never know about it before (it was published in 2021)?? This is wonderful information for those who put a box around what SLPs can do. I can't wait to dive in some more! So cool @slp.writer 😎

There's this tree by my house and it really puts on a show for about one week. My husband and I both agree it's the brightest red maple we have ever seen. I love nature 🍁 Ok, I know I say it a lot but I'm a summer person, but trees changing color is so fab

I bought the big mouth model!!! 👄 It is really fun to use with the students. The tongue is movable, but I wish it was a bit larger. "Ultrassist" is the brand and I bought it directly from them (NOT through Amazon because Jeff Bezos doesn't need my dollars). It costs about $30
